reviewText:
Significantly enjoyed this game; considering buying it after the free trial.

Pros:

- Logical, linear game flow;
- Well-designed mission objectives (almost entirely bug-free);
- Excellent graphics - really gives the feel of being a computerised tabletop;

Cons:

- Unit management is painful, although understandably so;
- Sometimes, NPCs' actions lead one to wish to bang their thick skulls together.

Overall, a nice, solid game. Would recommend.
